  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Response to COVID-19 with engagement of religious leaders in Kyrgyzstan</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="3">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">-	Members of Alert?s working group (by continuing dialogue with other religious and secular representatives)
-	Representatives of the State Commission on Religious Affairs (in particular the Department of Analysis and Evaluation and Centre for Studies on the Religious Situation)
-	Religious leaders (the ability to transfer key messages around COVID-19 and tolerance to their constituents)
-	Religious men and women online influencers and their audiences 
-	Religious communities (particularly those which do not engage constructively with secular government)

Beneficiaries include:
-	Representatives of government and media (as a result of the guidelines on sensitivity)
-	General public (through the communications campaigns)</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">To reduce the vulnerability of religious communities to COVID-19 through sensitive messaging and through the empowerment of the State Commission on Religious Affairs and religious figures to mitigate secular-religious tension in virtual spaces and, in so doing, help connect religious communities to wider (secular) society in Kyrgyzstan.</narrative>
  </description>
